The Western Cape Provincial Treasury has released the first-ever Procurement Disclosure Report. It details all personal protective equipment bought and paid for by the Western Cape government, in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -The Western Cape Provincial Treasury has released the first-ever Procurement Disclosure Report. The report details all personal protective equipment bought and paid for by the Western Cape government, in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The report will be made available to the public. Hundreds of millions of rand have been spent on PPE since the pandemic broke out in South Africa. SUMMARY: Makhura speaks about PPE tender scandal The Western Cape has spent more than R400-million on PPE so far but officials say they can account for every cent spent. COVID-19 corruption: Makhura admits the rot is within "This report is the first of its kind. It disclosures in detail the procurement of PPE and it provides significant transparency and I think it goes a long way to mitigate risks ii the procurement system. So at the end of the day, we can ensure that the vultures who feed on COVID-19 do not settle in the Western Cape," said the province's Finance and Economic Opportunities MEC, David Maynier. Provincial Treasury has put a number of proactive support and compliance measures in place. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.